,Recommended,301320,14797545,"Posted: 8 March, 2015",all,Job Center,"I'm going to give a positive review on this game, but I am not a fan of it. It depends on your skill, me being me, I just mess around which is actually quite fun. However, when it comes to wanting to make a smooth, exciting realistic rollercoaster, it becomes difficult. Very difficult. This game is very time consuming in the way that it takes a long time to create a rollercoaster. You do get a feeling of accomplishment when you make a perfectly smooth coaster and it is the closest thing to building a rollercoaster virtually. It requires patience and skill to not get bored of this game. I don't have either of these. I'd play it every now and again, but not all day every day.  The actual state of the game is brilliant. I haven't come across a single bug, corruption or actually any issues at all other than my stupidity. Very neat and professional, finished and generally a really good game. Just be prepared to get bored of it if you're not the best coaster creator. It is harder than I expected. It is hard to create a smooth track, there's a lot of trial, error, deleting parts and rebuilding. If you REALLY want it, get it. If you don't really mind, don't bother. I would rate it: 9/10 for state and performance, 5/10 for coaster building because of the difficulty and 9/10 for simiulation (when you go on the ride). It's very impressive, just I regret buying it simply because I'm terrible at building on it."
