76561198167966861,Recommended,301320,15439327,"Posted: 18 April, 2015",all,whiteghettogingersnap,"This is an amazing roller coaster simulator. This is better than any other roller coaster game I've played. I tried Theme Park Studio, but it didn't work well enough for me. RCT3 is fun, but the design part of roller coasters isn't detailed enough, and you can hardly make anything realistic. But this is perfect. Not only can you be realistic (and actually stay withing good g-forces) but you can be extremely imaginative (or boring, if that's your thing). If I want to make a typical Arrow looper, I can. If I want to make a ginormous strata coaster that's 15,000 feet long, I can still do that. There are endless possibilities.So many new features have been added since NoLimits 1. The design interface is so much cleaner and modern. The track very rarely needs adjusting and moving like in the first game. You just hit ""Depump Vertices"" and it automatically smooths (unlike in NL1 where smoothing was never enough). Things like the g-force and speed combs are really helpful because you can design in comfortable constraints instead of testing every element.The graphics are also much better. I found NL1 graphics to be somewhat jagged and even blocky sometimes. NL2 has pristine graphics and everything is much more realistic. When placing trees, you can count the leaves individually. NL1 had trees that were very bunched together. Terra-forming is a lot better now. Terrain rises in a circular pattern instead of in a square pattern.And of course, there are many more coaster types. 4D, suspended swinging, and wing are just a few of the new coaster types available.10/10 - Perfect coaster designer. I would recommend this to anyone who is a fan of roller coasters."
