,Recommended,301320,24638543,"Posted: 31 July, 2016",all,BailsBach,"Probably the most realistic coaster designer I've ever played with. Yes, I said designer - even the physics are realistic. You're able to ride, design / build, and control. And yes, I said control. You're given access to a control panel which lets you control the ride from just ""automatic"" (which is the AI controlling it, or custom scripts), ""blocks"", which let's you control segments of the track and release the coaster manually. Or, full manual, which is the hardest of them all. Try to play with 3 coasters at once, it's impossible! Despite people commenting about a ""steep learning curve"", the editor is quite simple and is quite easy to learn once you've gotten yourself ""rolling"" (pun intended). I'm not very good yet, but with a bit of practice I suppose I'd be able to design many great coasters.Note -You're able to import custom models, sounds, scripts and more, but even the vanilla version is good enough to keep you excited for a good, long set of hours!Realism: 9.5/10Customisability: 9.5/10Overall: 9/10"
